{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895637373,"sessionID":"ses_28462dd76ffeppBFMumWErnXKU","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba0ed4b001w81noJasqWURuc","messageID":"msg_d7ba0d61d00156JIb738B5A3Nz","sessionID":"ses_28462dd76ffeppBFMumWErnXKU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b5c046f8726d40e68ebd94b0fbc00dd8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # delta-spec.md — client-go 类型客户端生成\n2: \n3: **AR:** AR-035 — client-go 类型客户端生成  \n4: **Module:** client-go  \n5: **Language:** Go  \n6: **Size:** L\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## REQ-001: Clientset Interface\n11: \n12: ### REQ-001.1: Clientset Discovery Interface\n13: \n14: **GIVEN** a Clientset instance created via `NewForConfig`  \n15: **WHEN** calling `Discovery()` method  \n16: **THEN** returns a `discovery.DiscoveryInterface` implementation\n17: \n18: ### REQ-001.2: Clientset RuntimeV1alpha1 Accessor\n19: \n20: **GIVEN** a Clientset instance  \n21: **WHEN** calling `RuntimeV1alpha1()` method  \n22: **THEN** returns a `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` implementation\n23: \n24: ### REQ-001.3: Clientset NewForConfig Constructor\n25: \n26: **GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config`  \n27: **WHEN** calling `NewForConfig(config)`  \n28: **THEN** returns a `*Clientset` with no error\n29: \n30: ### REQ-001.4: Clientset NewForConfigAndClient Constructor\n31: \n32: **GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config` and `*http.Client`  \n33: **WHEN** calling `NewForConfigAndClient(config, httpClient)`  \n34: **THEN** returns a `*Clientset` using the provided HTTP client\n35: \n36: ### REQ-001.5: Clientset NewForConfigOrDie Constructor\n37: \n38: **GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config`  \n39: **WHEN** calling `NewForConfigOrDie(config)`  \n40: **THEN** returns a `*Clientset` (panics on error)\n41: \n42: ### REQ-001.6: Clientset New Constructor\n43: \n44: **GIVEN** a `rest.Interface` implementation  \n45: **WHEN** calling `New(restClient)`  \n46: **THEN** returns a `*Clientset` wrapping the REST client\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## REQ-002: RuntimeV1alpha1 Typed Client\n51: \n52: ### REQ-002.1: RuntimeV1alpha1 RESTClient Accessor\n53: \n54: **GIVEN** a `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` instance  \n55: **WHEN** calling `RESTClient()` method  \n56: **THEN** returns a `rest.Interface` with correct GroupVersion and APIPath\n57: \n58: ### REQ-002.2: RuntimeV1alpha1 GroupVersion\n59: \n60: **GIVEN** the typed client's REST client  \n61: **WHEN** checking configuration  \n62: **THEN** GroupVersion equals `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and APIPath equals `/apis`\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ## REQ-003: AgentRuntime Interface\n67: \n68: ### REQ-003.1: AgentRuntime Create\n69: \n70: **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` for namespace \"default\"  \n71: **WHEN** calling `Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})`  \n72: **THEN** creates the AgentRuntime resource and returns the created object\n73: \n74: ### REQ-003.2: AgentRuntime Update\n75: \n76: **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime resource  \n77: **WHEN** calling `Update(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`  \n78: **THEN** updates the AgentRuntime resource and returns the updated object\n79: \n80: ### REQ-003.3: AgentRuntime UpdateStatus\n81: \n82: **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime resource with modified status  \n83: **WHEN** calling `UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`  \n84: **THEN** updates only the status subresource\n85: \n86: ### REQ-003.4: AgentRuntime Delete\n87: \n88: **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-ar\"  \n89: **WHEN** calling `Delete(ctx, \"test-ar\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})`  \n90: **THEN** deletes the AgentRuntime resource\n91: \n92: ### REQ-003.5: AgentRuntime DeleteCollection\n93: \n94: **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntime resources in namespace \"default\"  \n95: **WHEN** calling `DeleteCollection(ctx, metav1.DeleteOptions{}, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n96: **THEN** deletes all AgentRuntime resources matching the list options\n97: \n98: ### REQ-003.6: AgentRuntime Get\n99: \n100: **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-ar\"  \n101: **WHEN** calling `Get(ctx, \"test-ar\", metav1.GetOptions{})`  \n102: **THEN** returns the AgentRuntime resource\n103: \n104: ### REQ-003.7: AgentRuntime List\n105: \n106: **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntime resources exist  \n107: **WHEN** calling `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n108: **THEN** returns an `AgentRuntimeList` containing all matching resources\n109: \n110: ### REQ-003.8: AgentRuntime Watch\n111: \n112: **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`  \n113: **WHEN** calling `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n114: **THEN** returns a `watch.Interface` for streaming AgentRuntime events\n115: \n116: ### REQ-003.9: AgentRuntime Patch\n117: \n118: **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-ar\"  \n119: **WHEN** calling `Patch(ctx, \"test-ar\", types.MergePatchType, patchData, metav1.PatchOptions{})`  \n120: **THEN** patches the AgentRuntime resource and returns the patched object\n121: \n122: ### REQ-003.10: AgentRuntime Namespace Isolation\n123: \n124: **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` for namespace \"ns-a\"  \n125: **WHEN** performing any CRUD operation  \n126: **THEN** operations are scoped to namespace \"ns-a\" only\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## REQ-004: CodeInterpreter Interface\n131: \n132: ### REQ-004.1: CodeInterpreter Create\n133: \n134: **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterInterface` for namespace \"default\"  \n135: **WHEN** calling `Create(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.CreateOptions{})`  \n136: **THEN** creates the CodeInterpreter resource and returns the created object\n137: \n138: ### REQ-004.2: CodeInterpreter Update\n139: \n140: **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter resource  \n141: **WHEN** calling `Update(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`  \n142: **THEN** updates the CodeInterpreter resource and returns the updated object\n143: \n144: ### REQ-004.3: CodeInterpreter UpdateStatus\n145: \n146: **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter resource with modified status  \n147: **WHEN** calling `UpdateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`  \n148: **THEN** updates only the status subresource\n149: \n150: ### REQ-004.4: CodeInterpreter Delete\n151: \n152: **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named \"test-ci\"  \n153: **WHEN** calling `Delete(ctx, \"test-ci\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})`  \n154: **THEN** deletes the CodeInterpreter resource\n155: \n156: ### REQ-004.5: CodeInterpreter DeleteCollection\n157: \n158: **GIVEN** multiple CodeInterpreter resources in namespace \"default\"  \n159: **WHEN** calling `DeleteCollection(ctx, metav1.DeleteOptions{}, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n160: **THEN** deletes all CodeInterpreter resources matching the list options\n161: \n162: ### REQ-004.6: CodeInterpreter Get\n163: \n164: **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named \"test-ci\"  \n165: **WHEN** calling `Get(ctx, \"test-ci\", metav1.GetOptions{})`  \n166: **THEN** returns the CodeInterpreter resource\n167: \n168: ### REQ-004.7: CodeInterpreter List\n169: \n170: **GIVEN** multiple CodeInterpreter resources exist  \n171: **WHEN** calling `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n172: **THEN** returns a `CodeInterpreterList` containing all matching resources\n173: \n174: ### REQ-004.8: CodeInterpreter Watch\n175: \n176: **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterInterface`  \n177: **WHEN** calling `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n178: **THEN** returns a `watch.Interface` for streaming CodeInterpreter events\n179: \n180: ### REQ-004.9: CodeInterpreter Patch\n181: \n182: **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named \"test-ci\"  \n183: **WHEN** calling `Patch(ctx, \"test-ci\", types.MergePatchType, patchData, metav1.PatchOptions{})`  \n184: **THEN** patches the CodeInterpreter resource and returns the patched object\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## REQ-005: Scheme Registration\n189: \n190: ### REQ-005.1: Scheme and Codecs Initialization\n191: \n192: **GIVEN** the `clientset/versioned/scheme` package  \n193: **WHEN** importing the package  \n194: **THEN** `Scheme`, `Codecs`, and `ParameterCodec` are initialized and available\n195: \n196: ### REQ-005.2: AddToScheme Registration\n197: \n198: **GIVEN** a new `runtime.Scheme`  \n199: **WHEN** calling `scheme.AddToScheme(scheme.Scheme)`  \n200: **THEN** registers all `runtime/v1alpha1` types (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter) to the scheme\n201: \n202: ---\n203: \n204: ## REQ-006: SharedInformerFactory\n205: \n206: ### REQ-006.1: SharedInformerFactory New\n207: \n208: **GIVEN** a Clientset and resync period of 10 minutes  \n209: **WHEN** calling `NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, resyncPeriod)`  \n210: **THEN** returns a `SharedInformerFactory` instance\n211: \n212: ### REQ-006.2: SharedInformerFactory Start\n213: \n214: **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`  \n215: **WHEN** calling `Start(stopCh)`  \n216: **THEN** all registered informers begin syncing\n217: \n218: ### REQ-006.3: SharedInformerFactory Shutdown\n219: \n220: **GIVEN** a running `SharedInformerFactory`  \n221: **WHEN** calling `Shutdown()`  \n222: **THEN** all informers stop and caches are cleared\n223: \n224: ### REQ-006.4: SharedInformerFactory WaitForCacheSync\n225: \n226: **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` with started informers  \n227: **WHEN** calling `WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)`  \n228: **THEN** blocks until all caches are synced and returns a map of synced types\n229: \n230: ### REQ-006.5: SharedInformerFactory WithNamespace\n231: \n232: **GIVEN** `SharedInformerFactoryWithOptions` with `WithNamespace(\"my-ns\")` option  \n233: **WHEN** creating the factory  \n234: **THEN** all informers are scoped to namespace \"my-ns\"\n235: \n236: ### REQ-006.6: SharedInformerFactory WithTweakListOptions\n237: \n238: **GIVEN** `SharedInformerFactoryWithOptions` with `WithTweakListOptions` option  \n239: **WHEN** informers perform List operations  \n240: **THEN** the tweak function modifies ListOptions before each list call\n241: \n242: ### REQ-006.7: SharedInformerFactory WithCustomResyncConfig\n243: \n244: **GIVEN** `SharedInformerFactoryWithOptions` with `WithCustomResyncConfig` option  \n245: **WHEN** creating the factory  \n246: **THEN** specific informers use custom resync periods\n247: \n248: ### REQ-006.8: SharedInformerFactory WithTransform\n249: \n250: **GIVEN** `SharedInformerFactoryWithOptions` with `WithTransform` option  \n251: **WHEN** objects are added to the cache  \n252: **THEN** the transform function is applied to each object\n253: \n254: ### REQ-006.9: SharedInformerFactory Runtime Accessor\n255: \n256: **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`  \n257: **WHEN** calling `Runtime()` method  \n258: **THEN** returns the `runtime` group informer accessor\n259: \n260: ---\n261: \n262: ## REQ-007: Informer Group/Version Access\n263: \n264: ### REQ-007.1: Runtime Group V1alpha1 Accessor\n265: \n266: **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`  \n267: **WHEN** calling `Runtime().V1alpha1()`  \n268: **THEN** returns `v1alpha1.Interface` with informer accessors\n269: \n270: ### REQ-007.2: AgentRuntime Informer Accessor\n271: \n272: **GIVEN** the v1alpha1 interface  \n273: **WHEN** calling `AgentRuntimes()`  \n274: **THEN** returns an `AgentRuntimeInformer`\n275: \n276: ### REQ-007.3: CodeInterpreter Informer Accessor\n277: \n278: **GIVEN** the v1alpha1 interface  \n279: **WHEN** calling `CodeInterpreters()`  \n280: **THEN** returns a `CodeInterpreterInformer`\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## REQ-008: AgentRuntime Informer\n285: \n286: ### REQ-008.1: AgentRuntime Informer\n287: \n288: **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInformer`  \n289: **WHEN** calling `Informer()`  \n290: **THEN** returns a `cache.SharedIndexInformer` for AgentRuntime resources\n291: \n292: ### REQ-008.2: AgentRuntime Lister\n293: \n294: **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInformer`  \n295: **WHEN** calling `Lister()`  \n296: **THEN** returns an `AgentRuntimeLister` for listing cached AgentRuntime resources\n297: \n298: ### REQ-008.3: AgentRuntime NewAgentRuntimeInformer\n299: \n300: **GIVEN** a Clientset and resync period  \n301: **WHEN** calling `NewAgentRuntimeInformer(client, namespace, resyncPeriod, indexers)`  \n302: **THEN** creates a `SharedIndexInformer` for AgentRuntime resources in the specified namespace\n303: \n304: ### REQ-008.4: AgentRuntime NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer\n305: \n306: **GIVEN** a Clientset, resync period, and tweak function  \n307: **WHEN** calling `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer(client, namespace, resyncPeriod, indexers, tweakListOptions)`  \n308: **THEN** creates a `SharedIndexInformer` with custom list options\n309: \n310: ---\n311: \n312: ## REQ-009: CodeInterpreter Informer\n313: \n314: ### REQ-009.1: CodeInterpreter Informer\n315: \n316: **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterInformer`  \n317: **WHEN** calling `Informer()`  \n318: **THEN** returns a `cache.SharedIndexInformer` for CodeInterpreter resources\n319: \n320: ### REQ-009.2: CodeInterpreter Lister\n321: \n322: **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterInformer`  \n323: **WHEN** calling `Lister()`  \n324: **THEN** returns a `CodeInterpreterLister` for listing cached CodeInterpreter resources\n325: \n326: ### REQ-009.3: CodeInterpreter NewCodeInterpreterInformer\n327: \n328: **GIVEN** a Clientset and resync period  \n329: **WHEN** calling `NewCodeInterpreterInformer(client, namespace, resyncPeriod, indexers)`  \n330: **THEN** creates a `SharedIndexInformer` for CodeInterpreter resources in the specified namespace\n331: \n332: ### REQ-009.4: CodeInterpreter NewFilteredCodeInterpreterInformer\n333: \n334: **GIVEN** a Clientset, resync period, and tweak function  \n335: **WHEN** calling `NewFilteredCodeInterpreterInformer(client, namespace, resyncPeriod, indexers, tweakListOptions)`  \n336: **THEN** creates a `SharedIndexInformer` with custom list options\n337: \n338: ---\n339: \n340: ## REQ-010: Generic Informer Routing\n341: \n342: ### REQ-010.1: ForResource AgentRuntime\n343: \n344: **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`  \n345: **WHEN** calling `ForResource(schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"agentruntimes\"})`  \n346: **THEN** returns a `GenericInformer` for AgentRuntime resources\n347: \n348: ### REQ-010.2: ForResource CodeInterpreter\n349: \n350: **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`  \n351: **WHEN** calling `ForResource(schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"codeinterpreters\"})`  \n352: **THEN** returns a `GenericInformer` for CodeInterpreter resources\n353: \n354: ### REQ-010.3: ForResource Unknown Resource\n355: \n356: **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`  \n357: **WHEN** calling `ForResource` with an unknown resource  \n358: **THEN** returns an error indicating no informer for the resource\n359: \n360: ---\n361: \n362: ## REQ-011: AgentRuntime Lister\n363: \n364: ### REQ-011.1: AgentRuntimeLister List\n365: \n366: **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeLister` with cached resources  \n367: **WHEN** calling `List(labels.Everything())`  \n368: **THEN** returns all AgentRuntime resources across all namespaces\n369: \n370: ### REQ-011.2: AgentRuntimeLister List with Selector\n371: \n372: **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeLister` with cached resources labeled `app=test`  \n373: **WHEN** calling `List(labelSelector)` where selector matches `app=test`  \n374: **THEN** returns only AgentRuntime resources matching the label selector\n375: \n376: ### REQ-011.3: AgentRuntimeLister Namespace Accessor\n377: \n378: **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeLister`  \n379: **WHEN** calling `AgentRuntimes(\"my-ns\")`  \n380: **THEN** returns an `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` scoped to namespace \"my-ns\"\n381: \n382: ### REQ-011.4: AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister List\n383: \n384: **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` for namespace \"my-ns\"  \n385: **WHEN** calling `List(labels.Everything())`  \n386: **THEN** returns all AgentRuntime resources in namespace \"my-ns\"\n387: \n388: ### REQ-011.5: AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister Get\n389: \n390: **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` with a cached AgentRuntime named \"test-ar\"  \n391: **WHEN** calling `Get(\"test-ar\")`  \n392: **THEN** returns the AgentRuntime resource\n393: \n394: ### REQ-011.6: AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister Get Not Found\n395: \n396: **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` without a cached AgentRuntime named \"missing\"  \n397: **WHEN** calling `Get(\"missing\")`  \n398: **THEN** returns an error matching `errors.IsNotFound`\n399: \n400: ---\n401: \n402: ## REQ-012: CodeInterpreter Lister\n403: \n404: ### REQ-012.1: CodeInterpreterLister List\n405: \n406: **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterLister` with cached resources  \n407: **WHEN** calling `List(labels.Everything())`  \n408: **THEN** returns all CodeInterpreter resources across all namespaces\n409: \n410: ### REQ-012.2: CodeInterpreterLister List with Selector\n411: \n412: **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterLister` with cached resources labeled `env=prod`  \n413: **WHEN** calling `List(labelSelector)` where selector matches `env=prod`  \n414: **THEN** returns only CodeInterpreter resources matching the label selector\n415: \n416: ### REQ-012.3: CodeInterpreterLister Namespace Accessor\n417: \n418: **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterLister`  \n419: **WHEN** calling `CodeInterpreters(\"my-ns\")`  \n420: **THEN** returns a `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` scoped to namespace \"my-ns\"\n421: \n422: ### REQ-012.4: CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister List\n423: \n424: **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` for namespace \"my-ns\"  \n425: **WHEN** calling `List(labels.Everything())`  \n426: **THEN** returns all CodeInterpreter resources in namespace \"my-ns\"\n427: \n428: ### REQ-012.5: CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister Get\n429: \n430: **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` with a cached CodeInterpreter named \"test-ci\"  \n431: **WHEN** calling `Get(\"test-ci\")`  \n432: **THEN** returns the CodeInterpreter resource\n433: \n434: ### REQ-012.6: CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister Get Not Found\n435: \n436: **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` without a cached CodeInterpreter named \"missing\"  \n437: **WHEN** calling `Get(\"missing\")`  \n438: **THEN** returns an error matching `errors.IsNotFound`\n439: \n440: ---\n441: \n442: ## REQ-013: Fake Clientset\n443: \n444: ### REQ-013.1: FakeClientset NewSimpleClientset\n445: \n446: **GIVEN** no pre-existing objects  \n447: **WHEN** calling `NewSimpleClientset()`  \n448: **THEN** returns a fake Clientset with an empty object tracker\n449: \n450: ### REQ-013.2: FakeClientset NewSimpleClientset with Objects\n451: \n452: **GIVEN** a list of runtime objects  \n453: **WHEN** calling `NewSimpleClientset(objs...)`  \n454: **THEN** returns a fake Clientset with the provided objects in its tracker\n455: \n456: ### REQ-013.3: FakeClientset Discovery\n457: \n458: **GIVEN** a fake Clientset  \n459: **WHEN** calling `Discovery()`  \n460: **THEN** returns a fake discovery client\n461: \n462: ### REQ-013.4: FakeClientset RuntimeV1alpha1\n463: \n464: **GIVEN** a fake Clientset  \n465: **WHEN** calling `RuntimeV1alpha1()`  \n466: **THEN** returns a fake `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n467: \n468: ---\n469: \n470: ## REQ-014: Fake Typed Clients\n471: \n472: ### REQ-014.1: Fake AgentRuntime Create\n473: \n474: **GIVEN** a fake `AgentRuntimeInterface`  \n475: **WHEN** calling `Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})`  \n476: **THEN** adds the AgentRuntime to the object tracker and returns it\n477: \n478: ### REQ-014.2: Fake AgentRuntime Get\n479: \n480: **GIVEN** a fake Clientset with an AgentRuntime \"test-ar\" in namespace \"default\"  \n481: **WHEN** calling `Get(ctx, \"test-ar\", metav1.GetOptions{})`  \n482: **THEN** returns the AgentRuntime from the tracker\n483: \n484: ### REQ-014.3: Fake AgentRuntime List\n485: \n486: **GIVEN** a fake Clientset with AgentRuntimes in namespace \"default\"  \n487: **WHEN** calling `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n488: **THEN** returns an `AgentRuntimeList` containing all AgentRuntimes in \"default\"\n489: \n490: ### REQ-014.4: Fake AgentRuntime Update\n491: \n492: **GIVEN** a fake Clientset with an AgentRuntime \"test-ar\"  \n493: **WHEN** calling `Update(ctx, modifiedAgentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`  \n494: **THEN** updates the AgentRuntime in the tracker\n495: \n496: ### REQ-014.5: Fake AgentRuntime Delete\n497: \n498: **GIVEN** a fake Clientset with an AgentRuntime \"test-ar\"  \n499: **WHEN** calling `Delete(ctx, \"test-ar\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})`  \n500: **THEN** removes the AgentRuntime from the tracker\n501: \n502: ### REQ-014.6: Fake CodeInterpreter Create\n503: \n504: **GIVEN** a fake `CodeInterpreterInterface`  \n505: **WHEN** calling `Create(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.CreateOptions{})`  \n506: **THEN** adds the CodeInterpreter to the object tracker and returns it\n507: \n508: ### REQ-014.7: Fake CodeInterpreter Get\n509: \n510: **GIVEN** a fake Clientset with a CodeInterpreter \"test-ci\" in namespace \"default\"  \n511: **WHEN** calling `Get(ctx, \"test-ci\", metav1.GetOptions{})`  \n512: **THEN** returns the CodeInterpreter from the tracker\n513: \n514: ### REQ-014.8: Fake CodeInterpreter List\n515: \n516: **GIVEN** a fake Clientset with CodeInterpreters in namespace \"default\"  \n517: **WHEN** calling `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n518: **THEN** returns a `CodeInterpreterList` containing all CodeInterpreters in \"default\"\n519: \n520: ---\n521: \n522: ## REQ-015: Expansion Interfaces\n523: \n524: ### REQ-015.1: AgentRuntimeExpansion Empty Interface\n525: \n526: **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeExpansion` interface in `generated_expansion.go`  \n527: **WHEN** inspecting the interface definition  \n528: **THEN** the interface is empty (reserved for custom methods)\n529: \n530: ### REQ-015.2: CodeInterpreterExpansion Empty Interface\n531: \n532: **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterExpansion` interface in `generated_expansion.go`  \n533: **WHEN** inspecting the interface definition  \n534: **THEN** the interface is empty (reserved for custom methods)\n535: \n536: ### REQ-015.3: AgentRuntimeListerExpansion Empty Interface\n537: \n538: **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeListerExpansion` interface in `expansion_generated.go`  \n539: **WHEN** inspecting the interface definition  \n540: **THEN** the interface is empty (reserved for custom lister methods)\n541: \n542: ### REQ-015.4: CodeInterpreterListerExpansion Empty Interface\n543: \n544: **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterListerExpansion` interface in `expansion_generated.go`  \n545: **WHEN** inspecting the interface definition  \n546: **THEN** the interface is empty (reserved for custom lister methods)\n547: \n548: ---\n549: \n550: ## REQ-016: Internal Interfaces\n551: \n552: ### REQ-016.1: NewInformerFunc Signature\n553: \n554: **GIVEN** the `internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc` type  \n555: **WHEN** inspecting the function signature  \n556: **THEN** it matches `func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer`\n557: \n558: ### REQ-016.2: TweakListOptionsFunc Signature\n559: \n560: **GIVEN** the `internalinterfaces.TweakListOptionsFunc` type  \n561: **WHEN** inspecting the function signature  \n562: **THEN** it matches `func(*metav1.ListOptions)`\n563: \n564: ---\n565: \n566: ## REQ-017: REST Resource Plural Names\n567: \n568: ### REQ-017.1: AgentRuntime Resource Plural\n569: \n570: **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`  \n571: **WHEN** performing REST operations  \n572: **THEN** the resource plural name is `agentruntimes`\n573: \n574: ### REQ-017.2: CodeInterpreter Resource Plural\n575: \n576: **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterInterface`  \n577: **WHEN** performing REST operations  \n578: **THEN** the resource plural name is `codeinterpreters`\n579: \n580: ---\n581: \n582: ## REQ-018: Module Path\n583: \n584: ### REQ-018.1: Module Path Correct\n585: \n586: **GIVEN** the generated client-go code  \n587: **WHEN** importing the module  \n588: **THEN** the module path is `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n589: \n590: ---\n591: \n592: ## REQ-019: Regeneration\n593: \n594: ### REQ-019.1: Make gen-client Regenerates Code\n595: \n596: **GIVEN** the source CRD definitions in `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`  \n597: **WHEN** running `make gen-client`  \n598: **THEN** executes `hack/update-codegen.sh` using `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch` flag\n599: \n600: ### REQ-019.2: Generated Code Matches Source Types\n601: \n602: **GIVEN** regenerated client-go code  \n603: **WHEN** comparing generated types against source CRDs  \n604: **THEN** all types in `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` are generated (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n605: \n606: ---\n607: \n608: ## Implementation Files\n609: \n610: | Path | Role |\n611: |------|------|\n612: | `clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n613: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n614: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n615: | `clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n616: | `clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n617: | `clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n618: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n619: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n620: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n621: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n622: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n623: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n624: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n625: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n626: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n627: | `informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n628: | `informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n629: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n630: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n631: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n632: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n633: | `informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Small factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n634: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n635: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n636: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n637: \n638: ---\n639: \n640: ## Dependencies\n641: \n642: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n643: |------------|---------|---------|\n644: | `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes client library |\n645: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | API machinery types |\n646: | `k8s.io/code-generator` | v0.34.1 | Code generation tooling |\n647: \n648: ---\n649: \n650: ## Validation Checklist\n651: \n652: - [ ] Clientset implements `Interface` with `Discovery()` and `RuntimeV1alpha1()` methods\n653: - [ ] `NewForConfig`, `NewForConfigAndClient`, `NewForConfigOrDie`, `New` constructors work correctly\n654: - [ ] `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` provides correct REST client configuration\n655: - [ ] `AgentRuntimeInterface` implements all CRUD operations (Create, Update, UpdateStatus, Delete, DeleteCollection, Get, List, Watch, Patch)\n656: - [ ] `CodeInterpreterInterface` implements all CRUD operations\n657: - [ ] Scheme registers all types via `AddToScheme`\n658: - [ ] `SharedInformerFactory` supports Start, Shutdown, WaitForCacheSync\n659: - [ ] Informer options (WithNamespace, WithTweakListOptions, WithCustomResyncConfig, WithTransform) work correctly\n660: - [ ] `AgentRuntimeInformer` and `CodeInterpreterInformer` provide Informer() and Lister() methods\n661: - [ ] `ForResource` routes to correct informers for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters`\n662: - [ ] Listers support List with selectors and namespace-scoped Get\n663: - [ ] Fake clientset supports object tracking for testing\n664: - [ ] Expansion interfaces are empty (reserved for extension)\n665: - [ ] Module path is `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n666: - [ ] `make gen-client` regenerates all code correctly\n\n(End of file - total 666 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# delta-spec.md — client-go 类型客户端生成\n\n**AR:** AR-035 — client-go 类型客户端生成  \n**Module:** client-go  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: Clientset Interface\n\n### REQ-001.1: Clientset Discovery Interface\n\n**GIVEN** a Clientset instance created via `NewForConfig`  \n**WHEN** calling `Discovery()` method  \n**THEN** returns a `discovery.DiscoveryInterface` implementation\n\n### REQ-001.2: Clientset RuntimeV1alpha1 Accessor\n\n**GIVEN** a Clientset instance  ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775895637349,"end":1775895637368}}}}
