{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895803819,"sessionID":"ses_28462dd76ffeppBFMumWErnXKU","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba376c9001AidzEFrvkWBPUi","messageID":"msg_d7ba0edb2001N6p7nY1qVL1lU9","sessionID":"ses_28462dd76ffeppBFMumWErnXKU","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-9a5a39a17c9a473782fe98e5738040da","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# delta-spec.md — AR-038 Go Unit Tests (workloadmanager)\n\n## AR-038 — Go Unit Tests (pkg/workloadmanager)\n\n**Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L  \n**Base specs:** deployment/client-go.md\n\n---\n\n## OpenSpec Format\n\nEach requirement follows GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure for acceptance scenarios.\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: Error Types and HTTP Response Handling\n\n### Description\nThe workloadmanager package defines custom error types and a unified HTTP error response handler that maps errors to appropriate HTTP status codes and JSON response bodies.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: ValidationError returns 400 BadRequest\n- **GIVEN** a ValidationError with Field=\"name\" and Reason=\"required\"\n- **WHEN** HandleError is called with the error\n- **THEN** HTTP status is 400\n- **AND** response body contains `{\"code\": \"VALIDATION_ERROR\", \"message\": \"Invalid request parameter\"}`\n- **AND** Content-Type header is \"application/json\"\n\n#### Scenario: NotFoundError returns 404 NotFound\n- **GIVEN** a NotFoundError with Resource=\"agentruntime\" and Name=\"test-runtime\"\n- **WHEN** HandleError is called with the error\n- **THEN** HTTP status is 404\n- **AND** response body contains `{\"code\": \"NOT_FOUND\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: InternalError returns 500 InternalServerError\n- **GIVEN** an InternalError wrapping a database connection error\n- **WHEN** HandleError is called with the error\n- **THEN** HTTP status is 500\n- **AND** response body contains `{\"code\": \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", \"message\": \"Unexpected server error\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: ServiceUnavailableError returns 503 ServiceUnavailable\n- **GIVEN** a ServiceUnavailableError with Dependency=\"kubernetes-api\"\n- **WHEN** HandleError is called with the error\n- **THEN** HTTP status is 503\n- **AND** response body contains `{\"code\": \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Unknown error type defaults to 500 InternalServerError\n- **GIVEN** a generic Go error not matching any custom error type\n- **WHEN** HandleError is called with the error\n- **THEN** HTTP status is 500\n- **AND** response body contains `{\"code\": \"INTERNAL_ERROR\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Error type implements Error() interface correctly\n- **GIVEN** each custom error type (ValidationError, NotFoundError, InternalError, ServiceUnavailableError, ConflictError)\n- **WHEN** Error() method is called\n- **THEN** returns formatted string matching expected pattern\n\n---\n\n## REQ-002: MemoryStore CRUD Operations\n\n### Description\nMemoryStore provides thread-safe in-memory storage for SandboxInfo records with full CRUD operations, expiration tracking, and batch querying capabilities.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds new sandbox to store\n- **GIVEN** a new MemoryStore instance\n- **AND** a SandboxInfo with SessionID=\"session-123\", SandboxID=\"sandbox-123\", ExpiresAt set to 8 hours from now\n- **WHEN** StoreSandbox is called\n- **THEN** no error is returned\n- **AND** store.Size() equals 1\n- **AND** expirationIndex contains the sandbox's expiration time\n\n#### Scenario: GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves existing sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with a stored sandbox having SessionID=\"session-123\"\n- **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with \"session-123\"\n- **THEN** no error is returned\n- **AND** returned SandboxInfo matches the stored sandbox\n\n#### Scenario: GetSandboxBySessionID returns NotFoundError for missing sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with no sandbox for \"non-existent\"\n- **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with \"non-existent\"\n- **THEN** NotFoundError is returned\n- **AND** error type is NotFoundError\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSandbox modifies existing sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with a sandbox having Status=\"running\"\n- **WHEN** UpdateSandbox is called with Status=\"terminating\" and LastActivity updated\n- **THEN** no error is returned\n- **AND** subsequent GetSandboxBySessionID returns updated Status and LastActivity\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSandbox returns NotFoundError for missing sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with no sandbox\n- **WHEN** UpdateSandbox is called with SessionID=\"non-existent\"\n- **THEN** NotFoundError is returned\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with one sandbox\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandboxBySessionID is called\n- **THEN** no error is returned\n- **AND** store.Size() equals 0\n- **AND** GetSandboxBySessionID returns NotFoundError\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID succeeds for non-existent sandbox\n- **GIVEN** an empty MemoryStore\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandboxBySessionID is called with any sessionID\n- **THEN** no error is returned (idempotent deletion)\n\n#### Scenario: ListSandboxes returns all stored sandboxes\n- **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with 3 sandboxes stored\n- **WHEN** ListSandboxes is called\n- **THEN** no error is returned\n- **AND** returned list contains exactly 3 SandboxInfo records\n\n#### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes filters by expiration time\n- **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with one expired sandbox (ExpiresAt before now) and one active sandbox\n- **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called with now as threshold\n- **THEN** only expired sandbox is returned\n- **AND** active sandbox is excluded\n\n#### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes respects limit parameter\n- **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with 20 expired sandboxes\n- **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called with limit=5\n- **THEN** exactly 5 sandboxes are returned\n- **AND** results are sorted by ExpiresAt (oldest first)\n\n#### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes filters by LastActivity\n- **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with one inactive sandbox (LastActivity 30 minutes ago), one active sandbox, and one with no LastActivity set\n- **WHEN** ListInactiveSandboxes is called with threshold 15 minutes ago\n- **THEN** only inactive sandbox is returned\n- **AND** active sandbox and no-activity sandbox are excluded\n\n#### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes respects limit parameter\n- **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with 20 inactive sandboxes\n- **WHEN** ListInactiveSandboxes is called with limit=5\n- **THEN** exactly 5 sandboxes are returned\n- **AND** results are sorted by LastActivity (oldest first)\n\n#### Scenario: Clear removes all sandboxes\n- **GIVEN** a MemoryStore with sandboxes stored\n- **WHEN** Clear is called\n- **THEN** store.Size() equals 0\n- **AND** both sandboxes map and expirationIndex are empty\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrent access is thread-safe\n- **GIVEN** a MemoryStore\n- **WHEN** 100 concurrent StoreSandbox, 100 concurrent GetSandboxBySessionID, and 50 concurrent DeleteSandboxBySessionID operations run\n- **THEN** no race condition occurs\n- **AND** all operations complete without panic or deadlock\n\n---\n\n## REQ-003: SandboxLifecycleManager\n\n### Description\nSandboxLifecycleManager orchestrates sandbox creation, deletion, expiration checking, and status updates with Kubernetes API integration.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: DefaultLifecycleConfig returns expected defaults\n- **GIVEN** DefaultLifecycleConfig function\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** DefaultTTL equals 8 hours\n- **AND** DefaultIdleTimeout equals 15 minutes\n- **AND** DefaultMaxDuration equals 8 hours\n- **AND** GCInterval equals 2 minutes\n- **AND** DeletionTimeout equals 30 seconds\n\n#### Scenario: NewSandboxLifecycleManager initializes correctly\n- **GIVEN** a K8sClient, MemoryStore, LifecycleConfig, and Logger\n- **WHEN** NewSandboxLifecycleManager is called\n- **THEN** manager.k8sClient equals provided K8sClient\n- **AND** manager.store equals provided Store\n- **AND** manager.config equals provided config\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandbox removes sandbox from store and Kubernetes\n- **GIVEN** a SandboxLifecycleManager with sandbox stored in MemoryStore\n- **AND** sandbox having SandboxNamespace=\"default\", SandboxName=\"sandbox-123\"\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with sessionID\n- **THEN** sandbox is removed from store\n- **AND** Kubernetes Delete call is made with correct namespace/name\n- **AND** no error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandbox returns NotFoundError for missing session\n- **GIVEN** a SandboxLifecycleManager with empty store\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with \"non-existent\"\n- **THEN** NotFoundError with Resource=\"session\" is returned\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandbox handles SandboxClaim deletion when Kind is SandboxClaim\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with Kind=\"SandboxClaim\"\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called\n- **THEN** both Sandbox and SandboxClaim resources are deleted from Kubernetes\n\n#### Scenario: IsExpired correctly detects expired sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with ExpiresAt 1 hour ago\n- **WHEN** IsExpired is called\n- **THEN** returns true\n\n#### Scenario: IsExpired returns false for active sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with ExpiresAt 8 hours from now\n- **WHEN** IsExpired is called\n- **THEN** returns false\n\n#### Scenario: IsIdleExpired returns false for sandbox with no activity\n- **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with LastActivity zero value\n- **WHEN** IsIdleExpired is called with any idleTimeout\n- **THEN** returns false\n\n#### Scenario: IsIdleExpired detects idle timeout breach\n- **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with LastActivity 30 minutes ago\n- **AND** idleTimeout of 15 minutes\n- **WHEN** IsIdleExpired is called\n- **THEN** returns true\n\n#### Scenario: ForceDeleteSandbox removes sandbox with gracePeriodSeconds=0\n- **GIVEN** a stored sandbox\n- **WHEN** ForceDeleteSandbox is called\n- **THEN** sandbox is deleted from Kubernetes with GracePeriodSeconds=0\n- **AND** sandbox is removed from store\n- **AND** no error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: ForceDeleteSandbox succeeds even for non-existent session\n- **GIVEN** empty store\n- **WHEN** ForceDeleteSandbox is called with any sessionID\n- **THEN** no error is returned (returns nil for NotFound)\n\n#### Scenario: GetSandbox retrieves sandbox from store\n- **GIVEN** a store with sandbox having SessionID=\"session-123\"\n- **WHEN** GetSandbox is called\n- **THEN** SandboxInfo is returned correctly\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSandboxStatus modifies sandbox status\n- **GIVEN** a store with sandbox having Status=\"running\"\n- **WHEN** UpdateSandboxStatus is called with newStatus=\"terminating\"\n- **THEN** sandbox Status is updated\n- **AND** no error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: handleDeleteError returns nil for NotFound Kubernetes error\n- **GIVEN** an apierrors.IsNotFound error\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteError is called\n- **THEN** nil is returned\n\n#### Scenario: handleDeleteError returns ConflictError for Kubernetes conflict\n- **GIVEN** an apierrors.IsConflict error\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteError is called\n- **THEN** ConflictError is returned\n\n#### Scenario: handleDeleteError returns InternalError for other errors\n- **GIVEN** a generic error\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteError is called\n- **THEN** InternalError wrapping the original error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: determineDeletionReason returns MaxDurationReached for expired sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with ExpiresAt before now\n- **WHEN** determineDeletionReason is called\n- **THEN** DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached is returned\n\n#### Scenario: determineDeletionReason returns IdleTimeout for idle sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with ExpiresAt after now but LastActivity idle\n- **WHEN** determineDeletionReason is called\n- **THEN** DeletionReasonIdleTimeout is returned\n\n#### Scenario: determineDeletionReason returns UserRequest for active sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox not expired and not idle\n- **WHEN** determineDeletionReason is called\n- **THEN** DeletionReasonUserRequest is returned\n\n---\n\n## REQ-004: GarbageCollector\n\n### Description\nGarbageCollector runs periodic cleanup of expired and inactive sandboxes with configurable intervals, batch limits, and timeout controls.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: NewGarbageCollector initializes with defaults\n- **GIVEN** a SandboxLifecycleManager and interval=0, onceTimeout=0\n- **WHEN** NewGarbageCollector is called\n- **THEN** interval defaults to GarbageCollectorInterval (2 minutes)\n- **AND** onceTimeout defaults to 2 minutes\n\n#### Scenario: NewGarbageCollector uses provided values\n- **GIVEN** a SandboxLifecycleManager and custom interval=100ms, onceTimeout=1s\n- **WHEN** NewGarbageCollector is called\n- **THEN** gc.interval equals 100ms\n- **AND** gc.onceTimeout equals 1s\n\n#### Scenario: Start and Stop work correctly\n- **GIVEN** a GarbageCollector\n- **WHEN** Start is called then Stop is called after 50ms\n- **THEN** garbage collector stops cleanly\n- **AND** runLoop goroutine exits\n\n#### Scenario: runOnce deletes expired sandboxes\n- **GIVEN** a store with one expired sandbox and one active sandbox\n- **WHEN** runOnce is called\n- **THEN** expired sandbox is deleted\n- **AND** active sandbox remains in store\n\n#### Scenario: runOnce deletes inactive sandboxes\n- **GIVEN** a store with one inactive sandbox (LastActivity old) and one active sandbox\n- **WHEN** runOnce is called\n- **THEN** inactive sandbox is deleted\n- **AND** active sandbox remains in store\n\n#### Scenario: runOnce respects GCBatchSize limit\n- **GIVEN** a store with 20 expired sandboxes\n- **WHEN** runOnce is called\n- **THEN** at most GCBatchSize (16) sandboxes are deleted per run\n\n#### Scenario: runOnce continues on individual deletion errors\n- **GIVEN** a store with 3 expired sandboxes\n- **WHEN** runOnce is called and some deletions fail\n- **THEN** processing continues for remaining sandboxes\n- **AND** error is logged but not returned\n\n#### Scenario: GetStats returns current configuration\n- **GIVEN** a GarbageCollector with custom settings\n- **WHEN** GetStats is called\n- **THEN** GarbageCollectorStats contains current Interval, OnceTimeout, and IdleTimeout\n\n#### Scenario: SetIdleTimeout updates idle timeout value\n- **GIVEN** a GarbageCollector\n- **WHEN** SetIdleTimeout is called with new value\n- **THEN** subsequent GetStats returns updated IdleTimeout\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrent runOnce calls are safe\n- **GIVEN** a GarbageCollector with 10 expired sandboxes\n- **WHEN** 3 concurrent runOnce calls execute\n- **THEN** no race condition occurs\n- **AND** store size is at or below 10 minus deletions\n\n---\n\n## REQ-005: HTTPServer\n\n### Description\nHTTPServer manages the HTTP server lifecycle with chi router, handler registration, graceful shutdown, and timeout configuration.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: NewHTTPServer initializes with default config\n- **GIVEN** a Config and Logger\n- **WHEN** NewHTTPServer is called\n- **THEN** server.router is chi.Router instance\n- **AND** server.handlers is empty map\n- **AND** server.stopCh is initialized\n- **AND** server.store is MemoryStore instance\n\n#### Scenario: RegisterHandler stores and registers handler\n- **GIVEN** an HTTPServer and a Handler implementation\n- **WHEN** RegisterHandler is called with name=\"test\"\n- **THEN** handler is stored in handlers map\n- **AND** handler's Register method is called with router\n\n#### Scenario: Start returns error channel\n- **GIVEN** an HTTPServer with config.Addr=\":0\"\n- **WHEN** Start is called\n- **THEN** error channel is returned\n- **AND** server begins listening\n\n#### Scenario: Stop closes stopCh and shuts down server\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTPServer\n- **WHEN** Stop is called with context\n- **THEN** stopCh is closed\n- **AND** server.Shutdown is called with timeout\n\n#### Scenario: Router handles registered routes\n- **GIVEN** an HTTPServer with a route registered at \"/test\"\n- **WHEN** HTTP request is made to \"/test\"\n- **THEN** route handler is invoked\n- **AND** correct HTTP status is returned\n\n#### Scenario: NewHTTPServerWithClients initializes with K8sClient and Store\n- **GIVEN** Config, Logger, K8sClient, and custom Store\n- **WHEN** NewHTTPServerWithClients is called\n- **THEN** lifecycleManager is initialized\n- **AND** garbageCollector is initialized\n- **AND** provided store is used\n\n---\n\n## REQ-006: K8sClient\n\n### Description\nK8sClient wraps Kubernetes dynamic client, core client, and informer factory for managing Kubernetes resources and watching Pod state.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: NewK8sClient creates all components\n- **GIVEN** a rest.Config\n- **WHEN** NewK8sClient is called\n- **THEN** dynamicClient is created\n- **AND** coreClient is created\n- **AND** informerFactory is created\n- **AND** podLister is initialized\n- **AND** scheme includes corev1\n\n#### Scenario: StartInformers starts factory\n- **GIVEN** a K8sClient with informerFactory\n- **WHEN** StartInformers is called with context\n- **THEN** informerFactory.Start is invoked\n\n#### Scenario: WaitForCacheSync returns true when synced\n- **GIVEN** a K8sClient with started informers\n- **WHEN** WaitForCacheSync is called\n- **THEN** returns true if all informers synced\n- **AND** returns false if any informer not synced\n\n#### Scenario: PodLister retrieves pods after sync\n- **GIVEN** a K8sClient with a Pod in the fake client\n- **WHEN** informers are started and synced\n- **THEN** PodLister can retrieve the Pod by name/namespace\n\n#### Scenario: DynamicClient returns dynamic interface\n- **GIVEN** a K8sClient\n- **WHEN** DynamicClient() is called\n- **THEN** returns the dynamic.Interface\n\n#### Scenario: CoreClient returns kubernetes interface\n- **GIVEN** a K8sClient\n- **WHEN** CoreClient() is called\n- **THEN** returns kubernetes.Interface\n\n#### Scenario: ClientCache GetOrCreateClient caches clients\n- **GIVEN** a ClientCache with rest.Config\n- **WHEN** GetOrCreateClient is called twice with same token+namespace\n- **THEN** same client instance is returned both times\n\n#### Scenario: ClientCache creates different clients for different keys\n- **GIVEN** a ClientCache\n- **WHEN** GetOrCreateClient is called with different token+namespace combinations\n- **THEN** different client instances are returned\n\n---\n\n## REQ-007: Config and Defaults\n\n### Description\nConfig struct holds HTTP server configuration with default values for timeouts, address, and health endpoints.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: DefaultConfig returns sensible defaults\n- **GIVEN** DefaultConfig function\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** Addr is \":8080\"\n- **AND** ReadTimeout is 15 seconds\n- **AND** WriteTimeout is 15 seconds\n- **AND** IdleTimeout is 60 seconds\n- **AND** ShutdownTimeout is 30 seconds\n- **AND** EnableHealthz is true\n- **AND** EnableReadyz is true\n\n#### Scenario: Config fields are accessible\n- **GIVEN** a custom Config instance\n- **WHEN** fields are read or written\n- **THEN** all timeout values and flags are accessible\n\n---\n\n## REQ-008: Constants and GVR Definitions\n\n### Description\ndefaults.go defines time constants, label keys, annotation keys, and GroupVersionResource definitions for Sandbox and SandboxClaim.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Time constants have expected values\n- **GIVEN** constants in defaults.go\n- **WHEN** values are checked\n- **THEN** DefaultSandboxTTL equals 8 hours\n- **AND** DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout equals 15 minutes\n- **AND** DefaultMaxSessionDuration equals 8 hours\n- **AND** SandboxCreationTimeout equals 2 minutes\n- **AND** SandboxDeleteTimeout equals 30 seconds\n- **AND** InformerSyncTimeout equals 1 minute\n- **AND** GarbageCollectorInterval equals 2 minutes\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxGVR has correct GroupVersionResource\n- **GIVEN** SandboxGVR variable\n- **WHEN** inspected\n- **THEN** Group is \"agents.x-k8s.io\"\n- **AND** Version is \"v1alpha1\"\n- **AND** Resource is \"sandboxes\"\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxClaimGVR has correct GroupVersionResource\n- **GIVEN** SandboxClaimGVR variable\n- **WHEN** inspected\n- **THEN** Group is \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"\n- **AND** Version is \"v1alpha1\"\n- **AND** Resource is \"sandboxclaims\"\n\n#### Scenario: Label keys match expected format\n- **GIVEN** label key constants\n- **WHEN** inspected\n- **THEN** LabelKeySessionID equals \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n- **AND** LabelKeyWorkloadName equals \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\n- **AND** LabelKeySandboxName equals \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n\n---\n\n## REQ-009: Router\n\n### Description\nRouter wraps chi.Router providing simplified routing interface with handler registration support.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: NewRouter creates chi.Router instance\n- **GIVEN** NewRouter function\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** Router wraps a chi.Router\n\n#### Scenario: RegisterHandlers calls Register on each handler\n- **GIVEN** a Router and multiple Handler implementations\n- **WHEN** RegisterHandlers is called\n- **THEN** each handler's Register method is called\n\n---\n\n## REQ-010: Informers\n\n### Description\nInformers wraps SharedInformerFactory for starting informers and waiting for cache sync.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: NewInformers creates from K8sClient\n- **GIVEN** a K8sClient\n- **WHEN** NewInformers is called\n- **THEN** factory equals K8sClient's informerFactory\n\n#### Scenario: Start begins informer factory\n- **GIVEN** an Informers instance\n- **WHEN** Start is called with context\n- **THEN** factory.Start is invoked\n\n#### Scenario: WaitForCacheSync returns sync status\n- **GIVEN** an Informers instance with started factory\n- **WHEN** WaitForCacheSync is called\n- **THEN** returns true if all synced\n- **AND** returns false if any not synced\n\n---\n\n## REQ-011: HealthHandler\n\n### Description\nHealthHandler provides /healthz and /readyz endpoints for Kubernetes probes with optional HealthChecker.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: healthz always returns 200 OK\n- **GIVEN** a HealthHandler with any HealthChecker (even nil)\n- **WHEN** GET /healthz is requested\n- **THEN** status is 200\n- **AND** body contains `{\"status\": \"ok\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: readyz returns 200 when checker IsReady is true\n- **GIVEN** a HealthHandler with HealthChecker.IsReady returning true\n- **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n- **THEN** status is 200\n- **AND** body contains `{\"status\": \"ready\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: readyz returns 503 when checker IsReady is false\n- **GIVEN** a HealthHandler with HealthChecker.IsReady returning false\n- **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n- **THEN** status is 503\n- **AND** body contains `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: readyz returns 503 when checker is nil\n- **GIVEN** a HealthHandler with nil HealthChecker\n- **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n- **THEN** status is 503\n- **AND** body contains `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Both endpoints return JSON Content-Type\n- **GIVEN** a HealthHandler\n- **WHEN** either /healthz or /readyz is requested\n- **THEN** Content-Type header is \"application/json\"\n\n---\n\n## REQ-012: DeletionHandler\n\n### Description\nDeletionHandler handles DELETE requests for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter sessions via SandboxLifecycleManager.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Delete AgentRuntime sandbox succeeds\n- **GIVEN** a DeletionHandler with valid sessionID in URL param\n- **AND** sandbox exists in store\n- **WHEN** DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/{sessionId} is requested\n- **THEN** status is 200\n- **AND** body contains `{\"sessionId\": \"...\", \"status\": \"deleted\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete CodeInterpreter sandbox succeeds\n- **GIVEN** a DeletionHandler with valid sessionID\n- **WHEN** DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{sessionId} is requested\n- **THEN** status is 200\n- **AND** body contains `{\"sessionId\": \"...\", \"status\": \"deleted\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete with empty sessionID returns ValidationError\n- **GIVEN** a DeletionHandler\n- **WHEN** DELETE request has empty sessionId\n- **THEN** status is 400\n- **AND** ValidationError for Field=\"sessionId\" is returned\n\n#### Scenario: Delete non-existent session returns 404\n- **GIVEN** a DeletionHandler with no sandbox in store\n- **WHEN** DELETE request is made with valid sessionID\n- **THEN** status is 404\n- **AND** body contains `{\"sessionId\": \"...\", \"status\": \"not_found\"}`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-013: CORS Middleware\n\n### Description\nCORSMiddleware adds CORS headers to responses based on allowed origins configuration.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Allowed origin receives CORS headers\n- **GIVEN** a CORSMiddleware with AllowedOrigins containing \"http://example.com\"\n- **AND** request with Origin=\"http://example.com\"\n- **WHEN** Wrap middleware processes request\n- **THEN** Access-Control-Allow-Origin is \"http://example.com\"\n- **AND** Access-Control-Allow-Methods and Headers are set\n- **AND** Allow-Credentials is set if configured\n\n#### Scenario: Disallowed origin receives no CORS headers\n- **GIVEN** a CORSMiddleware with AllowedOrigins containing only \"http://example.com\"\n- **AND** request with Origin=\"http://evil.com\"\n- **WHEN** Wrap middleware processes request\n- **THEN** no Access-Control-Allow-Origin header\n\n#### Scenario: Wildcard \"*\" allows any origin\n- **GIVEN** a CORSMiddleware with AllowedOrigins=[\"*\"]\n- **WHEN** any origin is requested\n- **THEN** origin is allowed\n\n#### Scenario: OPTIONS preflight returns 200 without calling next handler\n- **GIVEN** a CORSMiddleware with OPTIONS request\n- **WHEN** Wrap processes request\n- **THEN** status is 200\n- **AND** next handler is not called\n\n#### Scenario: No Origin header results in no CORS headers\n- **GIVEN** a request without Origin header\n- **WHEN** Wrap middleware processes request\n- **THEN** no CORS headers added\n\n---\n\n## REQ-014: Logging Middleware\n\n### Description\nLoggingMiddleware logs request details including method, path, status code, and duration.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Request is logged with details\n- **GIVEN** a LoggingMiddleware with Logger\n- **WHEN** request is processed\n- **THEN** logger.Info is called with \"request\"\n- **AND** args include method, path, status, duration\n\n#### Scenario: Status code is captured from response\n- **GIVEN** a handler that writes specific status code\n- **WHEN** LoggingMiddleware wraps handler\n- **THEN** logged status matches handler's written status\n\n---\n\n## REQ-015: Recovery Middleware\n\n### Description\nRecoveryMiddleware catches panics in handlers and returns HTTP 500 with error logging.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Panic is caught and 500 returned\n- **GIVEN** a RecoveryMiddleware and a handler that panics\n- **WHEN** panic occurs during request\n- **THEN** HTTP 500 is returned\n- **AND** logger.Error is called with panic details\n- **AND** \"Internal Server Error\" body is returned\n\n#### Scenario: Normal request passes through\n- **GIVEN** a RecoveryMiddleware and a normal handler\n- **WHEN** no panic occurs\n- **THEN** handler's response is returned unchanged\n\n---\n\n## REQ-016: HandlerFunc Adapter\n\n### Description\nHandlerFuncAdapter wraps function handlers to implement Handler interface with automatic error handling.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: HandlerFunc.ServeHTTP calls function\n- **GIVEN** a HandlerFunc implementation\n- **WHEN** ServeHTTP is called\n- **THEN** underlying function is invoked\n\n#### Scenario: HandlerFunc error triggers HandleError\n- **GIVEN** a HandlerFunc that returns an error\n- **WHEN** ServeHTTP is called\n- **THEN** workloadmanager.HandleError is called with the error\n\n#### Scenario: HandlerFuncAdapter Register adds route\n- **GIVEN** a HandlerFuncAdapter with Path=\"/test\"\n- **WHEN** Register is called on router\n- **THEN** route is registered at \"/test\"\n\n---\n\n## REQ-017: DeletionReason Constants\n\n### Description\nDeletionReason constants define reasons for sandbox deletion: IdleTimeout, MaxDurationReached, UserRequest.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: DeletionReason constants have correct values\n- **GIVEN** DeletionReason constants\n- **WHEN** inspected\n- **THEN** DeletionReasonIdleTimeout equals \"IdleTimeout\"\n- **AND** DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached equals \"MaxDurationReached\"\n- **AND** DeletionReasonUserRequest equals \"UserRequest\"\n\n---\n\n## REQ-018: SuccessResponse and ErrorResponse\n\n### Description\nSuccessResponse and ErrorResponse structs define JSON response shapes for HTTP endpoints.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: SuccessResponse contains Data field\n- **GIVEN** a SuccessResponse with Data populated\n- **WHEN** JSON marshaled\n- **THEN** output contains \"data\" key with provided value\n\n#### Scenario: ErrorResponse contains Code, Message, Details\n- **GIVEN** an ErrorResponse with all fields\n- **WHEN** JSON marshaled\n- **THEN** output contains \"code\", \"message\" keys\n- **AND** \"details\" is omitted if empty\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| REQ ID | Component | Test Count |\n|--------|-----------|------------|\n| REQ-001 | Error Types / HandleError | 6 |\n| REQ-002 | MemoryStore | 14 |\n| REQ-003 | SandboxLifecycleManager | 18 |\n| REQ-004 | GarbageCollector | 10 |\n| REQ-005 | HTTPServer | 6 |\n| REQ-006 | K8sClient | 8 |\n| REQ-007 | Config | 2 |\n| REQ-008 | Constants / GVR | 4 |\n| REQ-009 | Router | 2 |\n| REQ-010 | Informers | 3 |\n| REQ-011 | HealthHandler | 5 |\n| REQ-012 | DeletionHandler | 4 |\n| REQ-013 | CORS Middleware | 5 |\n| REQ-014 | Logging Middleware | 2 |\n| REQ-015 | Recovery Middleware | 2 |\n| REQ-016 | HandlerFunc Adapter | 3 |\n| REQ-017 | DeletionReason | 1 |\n| REQ-018 | Response Types | 2 |\n\n**Total Scenarios:** 77\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | Error types, interfaces, HandleError |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` | MemoryStore CRUD |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | SandboxLifecycleManager |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | GarbageCollector |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` | HTTPServer |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` | K8sClient, ClientCache |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/config.go` | Config struct |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Constants, GVR definitions |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` | Router wrapper |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` | Informers wrapper |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go` | HandlerFunc, HandlerFuncAdapter |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go` | HealthHandler |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_delete.go` | DeletionHandler |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go` | CORSMiddleware |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go` | LoggingMiddleware |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go` | RecoveryMiddleware |\n\n---\n\n## Test Files (Existing)\n\n| Path | Coverage |\n|------|----------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/types_test.go` | Error handling |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go` | MemoryStore CRUD |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go` | Lifecycle manager |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | GC operations |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go` | HTTPServer |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client_test.go` | K8sClient |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults_test.go` | Constants |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/config_test.go` | Config |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/router_test.go` | Router |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/informers_test.go` | Informers |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health_test.go` | Health endpoints |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_delete_test.go` | Deletion handler |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler_test.go` | HandlerFunc adapter |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors_test.go` | CORS middleware |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging_test.go` | Logging middleware |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery_test.go` | Recovery middleware |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go` | Integration tests |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | HTTP router |\n| `github.com/stretchr/testify` | Testing assertions |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | Kubernetes client |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | API machinery |\n| `pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo type |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Error types implement Error() correctly\n- [ ] HandleError maps errors to correct HTTP status codes\n- [ ] MemoryStore CRUD operations are thread-safe\n- [ ] MemoryStore expiration and inactive queries filter correctly\n- [ ] SandboxLifecycleManager DeleteSandbox removes from store and Kubernetes\n- [ ] SandboxLifecycleManager expiration/idle checks work correctly\n- [ ] GarbageCollector runs periodically and deletes expired/inactive\n- [ ] HTTPServer Start/Stop lifecycle works correctly\n- [ ] K8sClient creates all required clients and informers\n- [ ] Config defaults are sensible\n- [ ] Constants and GVR definitions match expected values\n- [ ] Router wraps chi.Router correctly\n- [ ] Informers Start and WaitForCacheSync work\n- [ ] HealthHandler /healthz and /readyz endpoints work\n- [ ] DeletionHandler handles AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter deletion\n- [ ] CORS middleware adds headers for allowed origins\n- [ ] Logging middleware captures request details\n- [ ] Recovery middleware catches panics\n- [ ] HandlerFunc adapter wraps function handlers","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-codin